<module>
    <h>bàta</h>
    <p><g>bàta</g>
        <en>a boat</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
            noun</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>adjectives</h>
        <p><g>bàta</g> can be the (deep) subject of certain <a href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives"
                >adjectives</a>.</p>
        <module id="baata_beag">
            <h>bàta beag</h>
            <p><g>bàta <a href="?gd=beag">beag</a></g>
                <en>a small boat</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha bàta beag air an traigh.</gd>
                        <tr>There is a little boat on the beach.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 21 [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </module>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h>prepositions</h>
        <section>
            <h>subject</h>
            <p><g>bàta</g> can be the (deep) subject of certain <a
                    href="?xx=prepositions/prepositions">prepositions</a>.</p>
            <module id="baata_air">
                <h>bàta air ...</h>
                <p><g>bàta <a href="?gd=air">air</a> ...</g>
                    <en>a boat on ...</en>.</p>
                <module id="baata_air_muir">
                    <h>bàta air muir</h>
                    <p><g>bàta air <a href="?gd=muir">muir</a></g>
                        <en>a boat on a sea</en> – <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Chunnaic mi bàtaichean air a’ mhuir.</gd>
                                <tr>I saw boats on the sea.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 21</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl></p>
                </module>
                <module id="baata_air_tiir">
                    <h>bàta air [tìr]</h>
                    <!--<p>When <g>bàta</g> is the subject of <g>air</g>, the object can be any common
                        nouns which denotes a piece of land, typically at the edge of the sea.</p>-->
                    <module>
                        <h>bàta air cladach</h>
                        <p><g>bàta air <a href="?gd=cladach">cladach</a></g>
                            <en>a boat on a shore</en> – <xl>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>An robh am bàta air a’ chladach? Bha.</gd>
                                    <tr>Was the boat is on the shore? Yes, it was.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 17 [adapted]</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl></p>
                    </module>
                    <module>
                        <h>bàta air tràigh</h>
                        <p><g>bàta air <a href="?gd=traaigh">tràigh</a></g>
                            <en>a boat on a beach</en> –<xl>
                                <li>
                                    <gd>Cha bhi bàta beag air an traigh.</gd>
                                    <tr>There won’t be a little boat on the beach.</tr>
                                    <ref text="617">td. 21 [adapted]</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl></p>
                    </module>
                </module>
            </module>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h>object</h>
            <p><g>bàta</g> can be the object of certain <a href="?xx=prepositions/prepositions"
                    >prepositions</a>.</p>
            <module id="ann_am_baata">
                <h>... ann am bàta</h>
                <p><g>... <a href=">gd=an^preposition">ann am</a> bàta</g>
                    <en>... in a boat</en>.</p>
                <module>
                    <h>[duine] ann am bàta</h>
                    <p><g>[duine] ann am bàta</g>
                        <en>a man in a boat</en> –<xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Tha an duine anns a’ bhàta.</gd>
                                <tr>The man is in the boat.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 17</ref>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Cha robh duine anns a’ bhàta.</gd>
                                <tr>There was no one in the boat.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 21</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl></p>
                </module>
            </module>
        </section>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <section>
            <h>object</h>
            <p><g>bàta</g> can be the object of certain (transitive) <a href="?xx=verbs/verbs"
                    >verbs</a>.</p>
            <module id="faic_baata">
                <h>faic [duine] bàta</h>
                <p><g><a href="?gd=faic">faic</a> [duine] bàta</g>
                    <en>[a man] sees a boat</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Bha mi aig a’ chladach an diugh. Chunnaic mi bàtaichean air a’
                                mhuir.</gd>
                            <tr>I was at the shore today. I saw boats on the sea.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 21</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl></p>
            </module>
        </section>
    </section>

</module>
